WEBVTT

00:00:01.856 --> 00:00:06.235 line:90% position:50% align:center
Welcome, everybody, to JW Broadcasting®.

00:00:06.235 --> 00:00:09.071 line:90% position:50% align:center
My cohost is Brother Izak Marais.

00:00:09.071 --> 00:00:12.533 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, his given name is Izak,
but we all call him Saki.

00:00:12.533 --> 00:00:16.871 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m so glad to see you, Saki,
because we’ve got a lot of work today.

00:00:16.871 --> 00:00:20.249 line:90% position:50% align:center
But first, you have
quite an interesting background in the truth.

00:00:20.249 --> 00:00:22.084 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why don’t you tell us something about it?

00:00:22.084 --> 00:00:23.168 line:10% position:50% align:center
Thank you.

00:00:23.168 --> 00:00:25.546 line:10% position:50% align:center
I’ll be happy to do so.

00:00:25.546 --> 00:00:27.548 line:10% position:50% align:center
I was born in South Africa

00:00:27.548 --> 00:00:29.425 line:10% position:50% align:center
in a very small town

00:00:29.425 --> 00:00:31.760 line:90% position:50% align:center
called Blyvooruitzicht.

00:00:31.760 --> 00:00:35.431 line:90% position:50% align:center
My father was not one of Jehovah’s Witnesses.

00:00:35.431 --> 00:00:40.227 line:90% position:50% align:center
He initially opposed my mother,
who was a dedicated servant of Jehovah,

00:00:40.227 --> 00:00:43.606 line:90% position:50% align:center
but later changed and was very supportive.

00:00:44.565 --> 00:00:46.942 line:90% position:50% align:center
My mother served Jehovah faithfully

00:00:46.942 --> 00:00:50.654 line:90% position:50% align:center
until her death in 2017.

00:00:50.654 --> 00:00:55.200 line:90% position:50% align:center
My grandfather and great-grandfather
on my mother’s side

00:00:55.200 --> 00:00:58.871 line:90% position:50% align:center
came into the truth in the early 1920’s

00:00:58.871 --> 00:01:00.915 line:90% position:50% align:center
simply by reading a tract.

00:01:02.374 --> 00:01:04.460 line:90% position:50% align:center
When I was about ten years old,

00:01:04.460 --> 00:01:08.547 line:90% position:50% align:center
I read the book
<i>What Has Religion Done for Mankind? </i>

00:01:08.547 --> 00:01:13.177 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I was convinced
that my mother had the truth.

00:01:13.177 --> 00:01:17.264 line:90% position:50% align:center
My two brothers and three sisters
also embraced the truth

00:01:17.264 --> 00:01:19.308 line:90% position:50% align:center
at an early age.

00:01:19.308 --> 00:01:23.395 line:90% position:50% align:center
And to this day,
all of them serve Jehovah faithfully

00:01:23.395 --> 00:01:25.397 line:90% position:50% align:center
in various parts of the earth.

00:01:25.397 --> 00:01:26.899 line:90% position:50% align:center
Good.

00:01:26.899 --> 00:01:30.319 line:90% position:50% align:center
While I was in my final year at school,

00:01:30.319 --> 00:01:33.530 line:90% position:50% align:center
I was invited to go to Bethel,

00:01:33.530 --> 00:01:36.033 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I started Bethel service

00:01:36.033 --> 00:01:40.663 line:90% position:50% align:center
in January 1965 in South Africa.

00:01:40.663 --> 00:01:43.916 line:90% position:50% align:center
Bethel was located in Elandsfontein,

00:01:43.916 --> 00:01:46.293 line:90% position:50% align:center
not far from Johannesburg.

00:01:47.461 --> 00:01:51.298 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Bethel family had only 55 members then.

00:01:51.298 --> 00:01:53.092 line:90% position:50% align:center
I had no particular skill,

00:01:53.092 --> 00:01:57.137 line:90% position:50% align:center
education, or training when I came to Bethel.

00:01:57.137 --> 00:02:00.391 line:90% position:50% align:center
Two older brothers in the small family,

00:02:00.391 --> 00:02:03.644 line:90% position:50% align:center
Andrew Jack from Scotland

00:02:03.644 --> 00:02:06.814 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Gert Nel from South Africa,

00:02:06.814 --> 00:02:08.899 line:90% position:50% align:center
took me under their wing because they knew

00:02:08.899 --> 00:02:12.361 line:90% position:50% align:center
I had so much to learn.

00:02:12.361 --> 00:02:16.156 line:90% position:50% align:center
They taught me how to apply Bible principles

00:02:16.156 --> 00:02:18.492 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the school of life

00:02:18.492 --> 00:02:22.121 line:90% position:50% align:center
as outlined at Proverbs 1:1-7.

00:02:23.580 --> 00:02:26.834 line:90% position:50% align:center
Andrew Jack taught me how to work

00:02:26.834 --> 00:02:31.130 line:90% position:50% align:center
and reminded me always to glorify Jehovah.

00:02:32.131 --> 00:02:37.386 line:90% position:50% align:center
Gert Nel, an Afrikaans translator since 1947,

00:02:37.386 --> 00:02:42.391 line:90% position:50% align:center
taught me how to reason
on Scriptural principles.

00:02:42.391 --> 00:02:45.394 line:90% position:50% align:center
Both of them finished
their earthly course long ago,

00:02:45.394 --> 00:02:47.771 line:90% position:50% align:center
but their example

00:02:47.771 --> 00:02:51.525 line:90% position:50% align:center
of loyalty still has a deep impact

00:02:51.525 --> 00:02:54.987 line:90% position:50% align:center
on the loyal servants of Jehovah
in southern Africa.

00:02:56.780 --> 00:02:59.199 line:90% position:50% align:center
I had several assignments over the years

00:02:59.199 --> 00:03:02.244 line:90% position:50% align:center
in Translation and in the Printery,

00:03:02.244 --> 00:03:05.080 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I worked mostly in cleaning assignments.

00:03:06.040 --> 00:03:08.459 line:90% position:50% align:center
In 1976,

00:03:08.459 --> 00:03:11.211 line:90% position:50% align:center
I married Jean,

00:03:11.211 --> 00:03:14.381 line:90% position:50% align:center
who served as a pioneer in Durban.

00:03:14.381 --> 00:03:18.635 line:90% position:50% align:center
She was born in Malawi,
but she grew up in South Africa.

00:03:18.635 --> 00:03:21.430 line:90% position:50% align:center
She set a great example for me

00:03:21.430 --> 00:03:23.432 line:90% position:50% align:center
by working diligently

00:03:23.432 --> 00:03:26.894 line:90% position:50% align:center
at every assignment that she was given.

00:03:26.894 --> 00:03:29.813 line:90% position:50% align:center
She always has a good attitude

00:03:29.813 --> 00:03:33.734 line:90% position:50% align:center
and works “as to Jehovah and not to men.”

00:03:33.734 --> 00:03:34.943 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hmm, very good.

00:03:35.652 --> 00:03:39.281 line:90% position:50% align:center
After serving at the South Africa branch
for a few years,

00:03:39.281 --> 00:03:44.286 line:90% position:50% align:center
we were transferred
to the United States Bethel in 1981.

00:03:44.286 --> 00:03:46.497 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ve served in Wallkill,

00:03:46.497 --> 00:03:48.874 line:90% position:50% align:center
Brooklyn, Patterson,

00:03:48.874 --> 00:03:51.418 line:90% position:50% align:center
and are now serving in Warwick.

00:03:51.418 --> 00:03:52.961 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, thanks for sharing.

00:03:52.961 --> 00:03:55.172 line:90% position:50% align:center
I know I’ve been built up
by hearing your experience,

00:03:55.172 --> 00:03:58.801 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I am sure the friends feel the same way.

00:03:58.801 --> 00:04:02.554 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why don’t you give us the highlights
of what we can expect during the program?

00:04:02.554 --> 00:04:05.307 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’ll be glad to, David.

00:04:05.307 --> 00:04:09.186 line:90% position:50% align:center
As this system nears its end,

00:04:09.186 --> 00:04:12.981 line:90% position:50% align:center
we may at times feel trapped and helpless.

00:04:12.981 --> 00:04:16.068 line:90% position:50% align:center
How can we be sure

00:04:16.068 --> 00:04:19.363 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jehovah is still helping us?

00:04:19.363 --> 00:04:22.491 line:90% position:50% align:center
Many years ago,

00:04:22.491 --> 00:04:26.745 line:90% position:50% align:center
Karen found joy and fulfillment
with her spiritual family.

00:04:26.745 --> 00:04:29.998 line:90% position:50% align:center
But her life serving Jehovah
hasn’t been easy.

00:04:30.833 --> 00:04:34.086 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ll see how she’s doing in the next episode

00:04:34.086 --> 00:04:38.507 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the series <i>Where Are They Now? </i>

00:04:38.507 --> 00:04:41.343 line:90% position:50% align:center
Have you ever wished that you could have

00:04:41.343 --> 00:04:44.096 line:90% position:50% align:center
more conversations in the ministry?

00:04:44.096 --> 00:04:45.722 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our latest episode

00:04:45.722 --> 00:04:48.851 line:90% position:50% align:center
of <i>Iron Sharpens Iron </i>

00:04:48.851 --> 00:04:51.270 line:90% position:50% align:center
provides suggestions for doing so.

