00:53:10.041 --> 00:53:12.752 line:90% position:50% align:center
What do you do in the ministry

00:53:12.752 --> 00:53:16.047 line:90% position:50% align:center
when it seems like no one is home?

00:53:16.047 --> 00:53:18.758 line:90% position:50% align:center
As we’ll see in this next episode

00:53:18.758 --> 00:53:21.802 line:90% position:50% align:center
of <i>Iron Sharpens Iron,</i>

00:53:21.802 --> 00:53:24.680 line:90% position:50% align:center
there may still be many opportunities

00:53:24.680 --> 00:53:27.475 line:90% position:50% align:center
all around us to give a witness.

00:53:28.184 --> 00:53:33.022 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hello, I am Victor Anibaba,
and this is <i>“Iron Sharpens Iron.” </i>

00:53:41.655 --> 00:53:43.657 line:10% position:50% align:center
Now, so far in our series,

00:53:43.657 --> 00:53:45.951 line:10% position:50% align:center
we’ve discussed how we can become

00:53:45.951 --> 00:53:48.079 line:90% position:50% align:center
more effective at our ministry

00:53:48.079 --> 00:53:50.081 line:90% position:50% align:center
in a number of different ways,

00:53:50.081 --> 00:53:52.958 line:90% position:50% align:center
such as by starting conversations,

00:53:52.958 --> 00:53:54.960 line:90% position:50% align:center
asking questions,

00:53:54.960 --> 00:53:57.546 line:90% position:50% align:center
and getting better at return visits.

00:53:58.172 --> 00:54:01.300 line:90% position:50% align:center
But these techniques only work

00:54:01.300 --> 00:54:04.553 line:90% position:50% align:center
if we actually find people to talk to,

00:54:05.679 --> 00:54:08.974 line:90% position:50% align:center
and sometimes
that can be our greatest challenge.

00:54:18.442 --> 00:54:21.445 line:90% position:50% align:center
Have you ever had days like this
in the ministry

00:54:22.154 --> 00:54:25.491 line:90% position:50% align:center
when it seemed
that there was just no one to talk to?

00:54:27.118 --> 00:54:29.203 line:90% position:50% align:center
If so, you’ll be pleased to know

00:54:29.203 --> 00:54:31.747 line:90% position:50% align:center
that our literature is full of tips

00:54:31.747 --> 00:54:35.709 line:90% position:50% align:center
that can help us
contact more people in our territory.

00:54:36.544 --> 00:54:39.713 line:90% position:50% align:center
In this episode,
we will consider three

00:54:39.713 --> 00:54:42.258 line:90% position:50% align:center
that have proved to be very effective.

00:54:42.925 --> 00:54:47.012 line:90% position:50% align:center
Tip number one: Be observant.

00:54:47.930 --> 00:54:52.309 line:90% position:50% align:center
There may actually be more opportunities
for us to contact people

00:54:52.309 --> 00:54:56.522 line:90% position:50% align:center
if we actually know where to look.

00:54:56.522 --> 00:55:00.276 line:90% position:50% align:center
Take for example our brothers and sisters
who we were just watching.

00:55:00.276 --> 00:55:03.571 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, it is true
that there was no one at home,

00:55:03.571 --> 00:55:06.991 line:90% position:50% align:center
but does that mean
there was no one to talk to?

00:55:07.992 --> 00:55:09.618 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, let’s see.

00:55:12.872 --> 00:55:13.914 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey!

00:55:13.914 --> 00:55:14.957 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hi.

00:55:14.957 --> 00:55:16.709 line:90% position:50% align:center
Your dog is so cute.

00:55:16.709 --> 00:55:17.710 line:90% position:50% align:center
What’s its name?

00:55:17.710 --> 00:55:18.794 line:90% position:50% align:center
Darleen.

00:55:18.794 --> 00:55:22.006 line:90% position:50% align:center
And just like that,
a conversation is underway.

00:55:24.300 --> 00:55:27.178 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, how about our couple
getting back into their car?

00:55:32.683 --> 00:55:35.436 line:90% position:50% align:center
By being observant,

00:55:35.436 --> 00:55:37.813 line:90% position:50% align:center
they too were able to give a witness.

00:55:37.813 --> 00:55:39.815 line:90% position:50% align:center
The more observant we are,

00:55:39.815 --> 00:55:41.859 line:90% position:50% align:center
the more opportunities we may find.

00:55:44.361 --> 00:55:48.324 line:90% position:50% align:center
The key is
to remain focused on our objective,

00:55:48.324 --> 00:55:50.993 line:90% position:50% align:center
which is to give a witness.

00:55:50.993 --> 00:55:53.954 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that can happen in between doors

00:55:53.954 --> 00:55:57.833 line:90% position:50% align:center
just as easily
as it could happen at the doors.

00:55:57.833 --> 00:56:01.587 line:90% position:50% align:center
So how about our tip number two?

00:56:01.587 --> 00:56:04.924 line:90% position:50% align:center
It is this: Be prepared.

00:56:04.924 --> 00:56:08.427 line:90% position:50% align:center
How often have you encountered someone
in your territory

00:56:08.427 --> 00:56:10.888 line:90% position:50% align:center
who doesn’t speak your language?

00:56:10.888 --> 00:56:15.017 line:90% position:50% align:center
You know, growing up in London,
this used to happen all the time.

00:56:15.017 --> 00:56:17.394 line:90% position:50% align:center
But these days,
it’s not just big cities

00:56:17.394 --> 00:56:20.898 line:90% position:50% align:center
where we find this mixture
of culture and languages.

00:56:20.898 --> 00:56:25.527 line:90% position:50% align:center
The whole world
is becoming so much more cosmopolitan.

00:56:25.527 --> 00:56:30.532 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what can we do to be prepared?

00:56:31.200 --> 00:56:33.202 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, we don’t have the gift of tongues

00:56:33.202 --> 00:56:36.121 line:90% position:50% align:center
like the first-century Christians did
at Pentecost,

00:56:36.121 --> 00:56:38.457 line:90% position:50% align:center
but we do have the gift

00:56:38.457 --> 00:56:42.836 line:90% position:50% align:center
of <i>JW Language®</i>.

00:56:42.836 --> 00:56:47.007 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now with this app,
you can learn a simple presentation

00:56:47.007 --> 00:56:49.260 line:90% position:50% align:center
in dozens of different languages.

00:56:49.260 --> 00:56:50.344 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s take a look.

00:56:51.595 --> 00:56:55.099 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s designed in a very easy-to-use manner.

00:56:55.891 --> 00:56:57.935 line:90% position:50% align:center
First,

00:56:57.935 --> 00:57:00.604 line:90% position:50% align:center
set the primary language
to the one you speak

00:57:02.648 --> 00:57:05.693 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the target language
to the one you want to learn.

00:57:07.945 --> 00:57:10.781 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then, under Preaching Skills,

00:57:10.781 --> 00:57:13.909 line:90% position:50% align:center
choose Greetings and Introductions

00:57:13.909 --> 00:57:17.246 line:90% position:50% align:center
to learn how to say a simple, “hello.”

00:57:19.206 --> 00:57:22.167 line:90% position:50% align:center
And “I am pleased to meet you.”

00:57:26.463 --> 00:57:31.135 line:90% position:50% align:center
<i>Dobryi den’</i>. 
<i>Pryyemno poznayomytys’a</i>.

00:57:32.386 --> 00:57:34.930 line:90% position:50% align:center
I think I’ve made a mess of that.
I best try it again.

00:57:34.930 --> 00:57:39.435 line:90% position:50% align:center
<i>Dobryi den’</i>. 
<i>Pryyemno poznayomytys’a</i>.

00:57:40.477 --> 00:57:44.732 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, I still need to work on my accent,
but I think you get the idea.

00:57:46.400 --> 00:57:50.654 line:90% position:50% align:center
With a little practice,
you can ask simple questions

00:57:50.654 --> 00:57:54.783 line:90% position:50% align:center
and even introduce and explain a scripture.

00:57:54.783 --> 00:57:58.662 line:90% position:50% align:center
It really works.
Let’s look at an example.

00:57:58.662 --> 00:58:01.081 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hi there,
we are making brief visits on our neighbors.

00:58:01.081 --> 00:58:02.708 line:90% position:50% align:center
No, no, no speak English.

00:58:02.708 --> 00:58:04.710 line:90% position:50% align:center
Oh, Arabic?

00:58:18.307 --> 00:58:21.101 line:90% position:50% align:center
What a great way to give a witness
to even more in our territory!

00:58:22.936 --> 00:58:25.939 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, if mastering a whole presentation
in another language

00:58:25.939 --> 00:58:27.983 line:90% position:50% align:center
seems a bit overwhelming,

00:58:27.983 --> 00:58:30.527 line:90% position:50% align:center
then here’s a simple suggestion:

00:58:30.527 --> 00:58:32.571 line:90% position:50% align:center
Just learn a greeting.

00:58:32.571 --> 00:58:34.573 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s only a few words,

00:58:34.573 --> 00:58:37.409 line:90% position:50% align:center
but don’t underestimate the power

00:58:37.409 --> 00:58:40.079 line:90% position:50% align:center
of greeting someone in their native tongue

00:58:40.079 --> 00:58:42.247 line:90% position:50% align:center
and with a warm smile.

00:58:42.247 --> 00:58:44.458 line:90% position:50% align:center
It can certainly open up doors,

00:58:44.458 --> 00:58:46.919 line:90% position:50% align:center
and it could also pave the way
for you to call back

00:58:46.919 --> 00:58:50.047 line:90% position:50% align:center
with someone who does speak their language.

00:58:50.047 --> 00:58:54.134 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that brings us on to our third tip:

00:58:54.134 --> 00:58:57.304 line:90% position:50% align:center
Be diligent and follow up,

00:58:57.304 --> 00:59:00.307 line:90% position:50% align:center
which, first of all,
means trying to contact

00:59:00.307 --> 00:59:02.893 line:90% position:50% align:center
all those who weren’t home initially,

00:59:02.893 --> 00:59:06.397 line:90% position:50% align:center
either on a different day
or at a different time.

00:59:06.397 --> 00:59:08.524 line:90% position:50% align:center
And if you can’t find them in that way,

00:59:08.524 --> 00:59:12.027 line:90% position:50% align:center
then don’t overlook
letter writing and telephone witnessing.

00:59:13.112 --> 00:59:15.697 line:90% position:50% align:center
These methods proved very effective
during the pandemic,

00:59:16.865 --> 00:59:19.284 line:90% position:50% align:center
and even now they can still help us

00:59:19.284 --> 00:59:22.079 line:90% position:50% align:center
to reach those we can’t find at home.

00:59:22.079 --> 00:59:25.833 line:90% position:50% align:center
Regardless of what way
we have contacted someone,

00:59:25.833 --> 00:59:29.044 line:90% position:50% align:center
please be sure not to forget them,

00:59:29.044 --> 00:59:31.046 line:90% position:50% align:center
but return promptly

00:59:31.046 --> 00:59:34.842 line:90% position:50% align:center
to follow up on any interest
that you have found.

00:59:34.842 --> 00:59:39.638 line:90% position:50% align:center
You know, reaching everyone in our territory
is definitely a challenge.

00:59:40.305 --> 00:59:43.058 line:90% position:50% align:center
But the tips we’ve discussed here today

00:59:43.058 --> 00:59:45.602 line:90% position:50% align:center
—(1) being observant,

00:59:45.602 --> 00:59:47.896 line:90% position:50% align:center
(2) being prepared,

00:59:47.896 --> 00:59:52.860 line:90% position:50% align:center
and (3) being diligent
as we follow up on interest that we find—

00:59:52.860 --> 00:59:57.114 line:90% position:50% align:center
can help all of us
fully accomplish our ministry.

00:59:57.906 --> 01:00:01.910 line:90% position:50% align:center
If we do that,
we’ll be imitating Jesus,

01:00:01.910 --> 01:00:04.246 line:90% position:50% align:center
who wanted to give everyone

01:00:04.246 --> 01:00:07.374 line:90% position:50% align:center
an opportunity to come to know Jehovah.

01:00:08.375 --> 01:00:11.545 line:90% position:50% align:center
What excellent suggestions for the ministry!

01:00:11.545 --> 01:00:13.547 line:90% position:50% align:center
I look forward to using them

01:00:13.547 --> 01:00:18.135 line:90% position:50% align:center
