01:02:33.395 --> 01:02:36.273 line:90% position:50% align:center
called <i>Learn From Jehovah’s Friends</i>.

01:02:37.441 --> 01:02:39.526 line:90% position:50% align:center
These short, animated videos

01:02:39.526 --> 01:02:42.654 line:90% position:50% align:center
will teach those
who are starting to read on their own

01:02:42.654 --> 01:02:46.450 line:90% position:50% align:center
about persons in the Bible who loved Jehovah.

01:02:47.034 --> 01:02:51.246 line:90% position:50% align:center
Look for it on JW Broadcasting soon.

01:02:52.873 --> 01:02:55.083 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our video postcard this month

01:02:55.083 --> 01:02:57.127 line:90% position:50% align:center
comes from a place known

01:02:57.127 --> 01:03:00.672 line:90% position:50% align:center
as the Land of Incorruptible People.

01:03:00.672 --> 01:03:03.133 line:90% position:50% align:center
Where might that be?

01:03:03.133 --> 01:03:04.593 line:90% position:50% align:center
The country’s name

01:03:04.593 --> 01:03:08.221 line:90% position:50% align:center
combines two words: “integrity”

01:03:08.221 --> 01:03:11.892 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the Moore language and “homeland”

01:03:11.892 --> 01:03:15.479 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the Jula language.

01:03:15.479 --> 01:03:20.484 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s Burkina Faso,
a landlocked country in West Africa.

01:03:21.777 --> 01:03:25.280 line:90% position:50% align:center
The first Kingdom publisher
arrived in Burkina Faso

01:03:25.280 --> 01:03:29.660 line:90% position:50% align:center
from Ghana in 1959.

01:03:29.660 --> 01:03:32.204 line:90% position:50% align:center
In 1972,

01:03:32.204 --> 01:03:34.414 line:90% position:50% align:center
the first of many

01:03:34.414 --> 01:03:37.501 line:90% position:50% align:center
intrepid missionaries arrived.

01:03:37.501 --> 01:03:40.212 line:90% position:50% align:center
And just two years later,

01:03:40.212 --> 01:03:42.881 line:90% position:50% align:center
congregations were formed in the capital,

01:03:42.881 --> 01:03:46.468 line:90% position:50% align:center
Ouagadougou, and in Bobo-Dioulasso,

01:03:46.468 --> 01:03:48.512 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the west of the country.

01:03:51.056 --> 01:03:54.059 line:90% position:50% align:center
Daytime temperatures average
around 30 degrees Celsius,

01:03:54.059 --> 01:03:57.312 line:90% position:50% align:center
or 86 degrees Fahrenheit,

01:03:57.312 --> 01:04:00.107 line:90% position:50% align:center
and may be much warmer
during the peak of the dry season.

01:04:01.566 --> 01:04:06.446 line:90% position:50% align:center
Often, a host will welcome visitors
with a drink of water.

01:04:06.446 --> 01:04:09.408 line:90% position:50% align:center
A common saying in the Moore language

01:04:09.408 --> 01:04:12.244 line:90% position:50% align:center
is <i>“Sãan la koom,” </i>

01:04:12.244 --> 01:04:15.622 line:90% position:50% align:center
which literally means “The guest is water.”

01:04:16.998 --> 01:04:20.293 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah’s people are working hard

01:04:20.293 --> 01:04:23.964 line:90% position:50% align:center
to take life-giving waters of Bible truth

01:04:23.964 --> 01:04:27.968 line:90% position:50% align:center
to the nearly 23 million people

01:04:27.968 --> 01:04:31.304 line:90% position:50% align:center
scattered in villages
through the savanna and forest.

01:04:32.973 --> 01:04:35.475 line:90% position:50% align:center
In March 2023,

01:04:35.475 --> 01:04:38.645 line:90% position:50% align:center
Burkina Faso reached a new peak

01:04:38.645 --> 01:04:42.941 line:90% position:50% align:center
of 684 auxiliary pioneers.

01:04:44.151 --> 01:04:47.988 line:90% position:50% align:center
Today, there are over 2,000 publishers

01:04:47.988 --> 01:04:50.031 line:90% position:50% align:center
in Burkina Faso.

01:04:51.158 --> 01:04:53.076 line:90% position:50% align:center
This is no small feat,

01:04:53.076 --> 01:04:57.247 line:90% position:50% align:center
owing to the travel difficulties
between villages

01:04:57.247 --> 01:05:00.250 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the 66 indigenous languages

01:05:00.250 --> 01:05:02.544 line:90% position:50% align:center
spoken throughout the country.

01:05:03.962 --> 01:05:06.673 line:90% position:50% align:center
Two remote translation offices

01:05:06.673 --> 01:05:10.677 line:90% position:50% align:center
produce literature
for the Moore and Jula languages.

01:05:11.636 --> 01:05:13.930 line:90% position:50% align:center
And in 2023,

01:05:13.930 --> 01:05:16.516 line:90% position:50% align:center
our brothers were overjoyed

01:05:16.516 --> 01:05:21.563 line:90% position:50% align:center
to receive the complete
<i>New World Translation</i>  in the Moore language.

01:05:22.105 --> 01:05:25.442 line:90% position:50% align:center
The brothers and sisters
from the Kamboincé Moore

01:05:25.442 --> 01:05:27.986 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Tampouy Moore congregations

01:05:27.986 --> 01:05:31.531 line:90% position:50% align:center
send their love and affection

01:05:31.531 --> 01:05:33.992 line:90% position:50% align:center
to the worldwide brotherhood!

01:05:33.992 --> 01:05:36.912 line:90% position:50% align:center
We hope you enjoyed our monthly program.

01:05:37.746 --> 01:05:40.290 line:90% position:50% align:center
And I want to thank you, Saki,
for all your help.

01:05:40.290 --> 01:05:41.917 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was really appreciated.

01:05:41.917 --> 01:05:43.084 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’re welcome.

01:05:43.084 --> 01:05:45.837 line:90% position:50% align:center
From the World Headquarters
of Jehovah’s Witnesses,

01:05:45.837 --> 01:05:49.466 line:90% position:50% align:center
this is JW Broadcasting.

